{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id52880554-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s610"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"610"},"text":"§ 610.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Courts defined","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"As used in this chapter the word “courts” includes the courts of appeals and district courts of the United States, the United States District Court for the District of the Canal Zone, the District Court of Guam, the District Court of the Virgin Islands, the United States Court of Federal Claims, and the Court of International Trade.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id52880555-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646"},"text":"June 25, 1948, ch. 646","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/915"},"text":"62 Stat. 915","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1951-10-31/ch655/s44"},"text":"Oct. 31, 1951, ch. 655, § 44","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/65/725"},"text":"65 Stat. 725","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/508/s12/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–508, § 12(e)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-07-07"},"text":"July 7, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/348"},"text":"72 Stat. 348","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598/tII/s226"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598, title II, § 226","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-06"},"text":"Nov. 6, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/2665"},"text":"92 Stat. 2665","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/417/tV/s501/15"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–417, title V, § 501(15)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-10"},"text":"Oct. 10, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/1742"},"text":"94 Stat. 1742","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/164/tI/s120/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–164, title I, § 120(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-04-02"},"text":"Apr. 2, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/33"},"text":"96 Stat. 33","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/572/tIX/s902/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–572, title IX, § 902(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-29"},"text":"Oct. 29, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/4516"},"text":"106 Stat. 4516","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id52880556-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id52880557-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 450 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s308"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 308","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1939-08-07/ch501/s1"},"text":"Aug. 7, 1939, ch. 501, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/53/1223"},"text":"53 Stat. 1223","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Words “and the United States Court for China” were omitted. See reviser’s note under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s411"},"text":"section 411 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Provisions making this chapter and sections 332 and 333 of this title expressly applicable to the Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia were omitted as covered by “courts of appeals.” (See ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s41"},"text":"section 41 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and reviser’s notes under such section and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s44"},"text":"section 44 of this title","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A definition of “continental United States” as “the States of the Union and the District of Columbia” is omitted as unnecessary. (See reviser’s note under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s333"},"text":"section 333 of this title","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “district courts in the United States” in this section includes the District Court for the District of Columbia. (See ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s88"},"text":"section 88 of this title","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Other provisions of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s450"},"text":"section 450 of title 28","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C., 1940 ed., are incorporated in sections 333 and 604 of this title."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The phrase “all other courts of the United States established by Act of Congress” was added to provide for future growth of the Federal judicial system. [See Senate Revision Amendment below.]","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Changes in arrangement and phraseology were made.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id52880558-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Senate Revision Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Those provisions of this section which related to the Tax Court were eliminated by Senate amendment. See 80th Congress Senate Report No. 1559.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id52880559-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id5288055a-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1992—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/572"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–572","children":[],"tail":" substituted “United States Court of Federal Claims” for “United States Claims Court”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1982—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/164"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–164","children":[],"tail":" substituted “the United States Claims Court” for “the Court of Claims, the Court of Customs and Patent Appeals”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/417"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–417","children":[],"tail":" redesignated the Customs Court as the Court of International Trade."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1978—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":" directed the amendment of section by substituting “, district courts, and bankruptcy courts” for “and district courts”, which amendment did not become effective pursuant to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598/s402/b"},"text":"section 402(b) of Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":", as amended, set out as an Effective Date note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t11/s101"},"text":"section 101 of Title 11","children":[],"tail":", Bankruptcy."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1958—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/508"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–508","children":[],"tail":" struck out provisions which included District Court for Territory of Alaska within definition of court. See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s81A"},"text":"section 81A of this title","children":[],"tail":" which establishes a United States District Court for the State of Alaska."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1951—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1951-10-31"},"text":"Oct. 31, 1951","children":[],"tail":", inserted reference to the District Court of Guam."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id5288055b-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id5288055c-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1992 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/572"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–572","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-29"},"text":"Oct. 29, 1992","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/572/s911"},"text":"section 911 of Pub. L. 102–572","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s171"},"text":"section 171 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id5288055d-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1